

	iNTRODUCTION TO TYPESCRIPT:


		Setup the TypeScript: 

		- Install Node.js  https://nodejs.org/en/download/
		- Verify the installation by open the terminal on macOS and Linux or command line on Windows and type the command node -v

			C:\Users\archer>node -v
			v14.18.1


		- Install TypeScript compiler

			Execute the command: npm install -g typescript

			After the installation, you can type the following command to check the current version of the TypeScript compiler:

				tsc --v

			C:\Users\archer>tsc --v
			Version 4.4.4


		- Install VS Code

			- install the Live Server extension



			//------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


				//  First Program in typescript

					- Create one folder open in the vscode

					- create a new TypeScript file called <File_name>.ts and write a code

						let message: string = 'Hello, World!';
						console.log(message);

					- launch a new Terminal within the VS Code by using the keyboard shortcut Ctrl+` or follow the menu Terminal > New Terminal

					 type the following command on the Terminal to compile the app.ts file:
							..> tsc <file_name> .ts

							* if everythimg all rigth then it will generate <file_name> .js


					- To run the app.js file in node.js, you use the following command:

							..> node <file_name>.js
















